article.headline: Murray St. 74, Morehead St. 62
article.story: MURRAY, Ky. (AP) -- Ray George had 15 points and five assists to lead Murray State to a 74-62 victory Saturday night against Morehead State. The Racers (13-12, 11-7 Ohio Valley Conference) never trailed after the 14-minute mark of the first half. After spotting the Eagles (10-14, 6-10 OVC) an 11-9 early lead, the Racers went on an 11-3 scoring run. The Racer defense held the Eagles to 40 percent shooting from the field and just 19 percent from beyond the 3-point arc. The Racer's lead grew to as much as nine in the first half, before Morehead State put together a 7-2 scoring run to go into halftime down by just four points at 33-29. Murray State led by as much as 15 in the second half. Morehead State turned the ball over 20 times, committing six more turnovers than it had assists. Six players reach double figures for the Racers. Ed Horton scored 11 points and dished out five assists while Tyler Holloway scored 11. Danero Thomas scored 10 points and pulled down five rebounds. Shawn Witherspoon and Marvin Williams both scored 10 points each. Shaun Williams led Morehead State with 12 points.
